<!DOCTYPE assessment PUBLIC "-//Carnegie Mellon University//DTD Inline Assessment MathML 1.4//EN" "http://oli.cmu.edu/dtd/oli_inline_assessment_mathml_1_4.dtd"><assessment xmlns:cmd="http://oli.web.cmu.edu/content/metadata/2.1/" id="endo_peptide_derived_digt"><title>tutor</title><page id="d6f8265d03b944758083c2110bb1cd20"><title>Assessment Page Title</title><question id="q1"><body><p id="ac5a98c777e8d40cf932b709ac5deb2c8">Which of the following is an example of a peptide hormone produced by the hypothalamus and stored in the posterior pituitary?</p></body><multiple_choice shuffle="true" select="single" id="fe258422c0364500aa65f4ecf8fc16da" labels="false"><choice value="A">follicle-stimulating hormone</choice><choice value="B">insulin</choice><choice value="C">epinephrine</choice><choice value="D">antidiuretic hormone</choice></multiple_choice><part id="i0547b5673fd14ea8a9bd073a391d33a8"><skillref idref="endo_peptide_derived_SKILL" /><response match="A" score="0"><feedback><p id="adfc41b1148a24a5ca3d3051e8ac01157">Incorrect. Follicle-stimulating hormone is produced by the pituitary gland but is a glycoprotein.</p></feedback></response><response match="B" score="0"><feedback><p id="ac02c2319d1f04b1488f7510fa4615d7f">Incorrect. Insulin is produced by the pancreas.</p></feedback></response><response match="C" score="0"><feedback><p id="ab0c44bb0ade14d26afe718762c21bef5">Incorrect. Epinephrine is an amino acid based hormone which is smaller than a polypeptide chain.</p></feedback></response><response match="D" score="10"><feedback><p id="ac25ac7f5ccdc46df8c02d0a26549ae1a">Correct. Antidiuretic hormone is a short polypeptide chain based hormone.</p></feedback></response></part></question></page></assessment>
